Introduction

BaBa was a female trio under PR Entertainment. They made their debut on March 24, 2015, with their first single "Sergeant Kim’s Return from Vietnam".

Since their debut in 2015, the girl group has gone through fifteen departures and additions of members over four years. Pureum is the only one who remains from the original lineup.

Despite the many changes in their members, BaBa continued to perform in 2019 with five new additions who planned to make their fourth return later that year. The final members of the group were: Pureum, Starlight, Sooreem, Chaeha and Johwa.

BaBa performed their new song “It will be pretty” on Radio Soda on February 10, 2020. They did not reveal when the song would come out. The song never came out as they disbanded on June 20, 2020.
